<item>
            <title>[LU-4747] sanity tests 120* call to &quot;lctl get_param ldlm.services.ldlm_canceld.stats&quot; on client fail</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4747</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity tests 120a, b, c, d, e, f and g all call &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lctl get_param -n ldlm.services.ldlm_canceld.stats
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;on the client, but the file /proc/fs/lustre/ldlm/services/ldlm_canceld is only on the MDS not the clients. Calling &quot;lctl get_param&quot; on the MDS will correct this problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, these calls to get_param fail to get the value they are looking for, but the test passes. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
